## 4 Kinetic energy

Kinetic energy of an object is the energy it possess by virtue of its motion.

\[E_{k}=\frac{1}{2}mv^{2}\]

Derivation of equation:

Consider an object of mass m moving to the right under a constant force \(F_{net}\). Then,

\[F_{net}=ma\]

