## 3 Coulomb's Law

To calculate the force acting on a charged particle due to another charged particle, we can use Coulomb's Law.

Coulomb's Law states that the electric force between two point particles carrying charges \(Q_{1}\) and \(Q_{2}\) separated by a distance \(r\) apart is proportional to the product of the two charges and inversely proportional to the square of their distance apart.

\[\begin{array}{c}F\propto\frac{Q_{1}Q_{2}}{r^{2}}\\ F=\frac{Q_{1}Q_{2}}{4\pi\varepsilon_{0}r^{2}}\end{array}\qquad\qquad\varepsilon= 8.85\times 10^{-12}\;\mbox{Fm}^{-1}\]

