The electric potential energy (EPE) between two point charges \(Q_{1}\) and \(Q_{2}\) separated by a distance \(r\) apart is given by

\[\begin{array}{c}U=\frac{Q_{1}Q_{2}}{4\pi\varepsilon_{0}r}\end{array}\]

EPE can be negative, if one charge is positive and the other is negative.

