Potential energy \(U\) and potential \(V\) is related by the equation

\[\begin{array}{c}U\equiv Vq\end{array}\]

Positive charges will move from places of high potential to places of lower potential.

Negative charges will move from places of low potential to places of higher potential.

Change in EPE by a particle moving between 2 points whose potential difference is \(\Delta V\) is given by the formula

